label: A_cP20_213_cd-001
title: $\beta$-Mn ($A13$) Structure
comments:
This is the high temperature form of manganese, stable in the range 727-1095$^\circ$C and metastable at room temperature (Donohue, 1982).  The ground state is \href{current_web_home_dir/A_cI58_217_ac2g-001}{$\alpha$-Mn ($A12$)}. 
 This structure may also be found in the enantiomorphic space group $P4_{3}32$ \#212.
